org.naomi.regex

Class FilterCharClass

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.naomi.regex.Pattern
      • org.naomi.regex.CharClass
        • org.naomi.regex.FilterCharClass
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AlterationListener

    public abstract class FilterCharClass
extends CharClass
    An instance of FilterCharClass is a Pattern which, on each repetition, matches any single character that lies inclusively (in the normal collating sequence) between getFirst() and getLast() and satisfies filter(Char). If the resulting set (which is not a java.util.Set) contains more than a few thousand characters, performance may be adversely impacted. The internal "Not" flag in each instance can be set to make the class instead match all characters except those in the pre-defined set denoted by getFirst(), getLast() and filter(Char); this has the effect of matching the complement of the specified set of characters.

    Example: 

      // Since FilterCharClass is abstract, its body is
  //    provided here to define the required methods

     // Select ASCII characters between 'A' and 'z'
     // whose two least significant bits are both 1

    FilterCharClass bits = new FilterCharClass()
      {
        public char getFirst() {return 'A';}
        public boolean filter(char ch){return (ch&3) ==3;}
        public char getLast() {return 'z';}

        public FilterCharClass copy()
        {return this;}
      };
